olive oil
1 Wholemeal Panini
1 packet chicken thigh
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 apple
1 carrot
½ lemon
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut or tear wholemeal panini into bite-sized chunks.
• Place panini on a lined oven tray, drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until golden, 5-7 minutes. Set aside to cool slightly.

• While the croutons are baking, combine chicken thigh and Aussie spice blend in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken until browned, 2-3 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray and roast until cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice apple. Grate the carrot. Slice lemon into wedges.
• In a large bowl, combine dill & parsley mayonnaise, a drizzle of olive oil and a splash of water.
• Add shredded cabbage mix, apple, carrot and croutons. Add a squeeze of lemon juice, season and toss to combine.

• Slice golden chicken.
• Divide crouton slaw with herby-mayo dressing between plates.
• Top with chicken, spooning over any resting juices.
• Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!